# Agentic Pipeline for Lead Automation

We will create an automated Agentic workflow orchestrating your local JavaScript tools, relying on n8n for workflow management, Gemini 3.1 Pro for AI synthesis, and a Browser Agent for downstream visual validation.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Do you already have an n8n instance running, or do you want me to write the `n8n_workflow.json` so you can manually import it into n8n? Alternatively, I can use `npx n8n` to run the workflow temporarily and trigger a webhook!
> - Regarding using the local files as "tools" inside n8n: Do you want n8n to call `server.js` as an HTTP endpoint, or should n8n independently execute short Node CLI wrappers over `aiService.js` and `sheetsService.js`?
> - For the "Manager View", I plan to create a living markdown Artifact dashboard (`manager_view.md`) that will reflect the real-time completion status of the webhook trigger, the AI summarization, the Sheets append, and the Browser validation. Does that fit your vision?

## Proposed Changes

### Files & Components

#### [MODIFY] aiService.js
- Upgrade the generated AI model inside `aiService.js` from `gemini-2.5-flash` to `gemini-3.1-pro` per your specification.

#### [MODIFY] server.js
- Refactor the code appropriately. If n8n will handle Google Sheets orchestration, `server.js` should only call `aiService` (or handle all if you meant n8n simply forwards the webhook to `server.js`). *We will use n8n to coordinate instead of keeping everything hardcoded in `server.js`.*

#### [NEW] n8n_workflow.json
- Generate the structured JSON definition for the n8n workflow. It will:
  1. Trigger from an n8n Webhook node.
  2. Call out to the local JS code to perform the summarization.
  3. Formally invoke the Google Sheets step (using local `sheetsService.js` or an HTTP request depending on answer).

#### [NEW] manager_view.md (Artifact)
- This will act as the "Manager View". It will be a dynamic dashboard tracking the progression of this specific pipeline.

## Open Questions

> [!WARNING]
> Please confirm how `server.js` and the services should fit into n8n exactly:
> 1. Should n8n be the ultimate pipeline controller calling HTTP endpoints on `server.js` acting as an API gateway?
> 2. Should I run the whole pipeline using a test lead right now to trigger the Browser Agent, or should I just set things up and wait for your actual lead?

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Build and save the n8n JSON file.
- Send a test webhook POST using standard tools (like curl) or a short Node script.
- Assert the spreadsheet row was added.

### Manual Verification
- After the automation logic fires successfully, I will immediately execute the `browser_subagent` task to navigate to `https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1WFmcSU5d8gCNAQm7Dp30lVtS6f0r8Idfzgo8wVVVSEw/edit`.
- The Browser Agent will verify the data on your sheet, and I will report the success on the Manager View artifact.
